<ResourceDictionary xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
                    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
                    xmlns:sections="clr-namespace:ReportHelper.ViewModels.Sections"
                    xmlns:views="clr-namespace:ReportHelper.Views.Sections">

    <!--
        SectionShellView's ContentControl binds Content to CurrentSectionViewModel
        (an ObservableObject, e.g. ReportHeaderViewModel). WPF has no way to know
        which View renders a given ViewModel unless told explicitly — that's what
        this file is for: one DataTemplate per section, each keyed by DataType to
        a ViewModel and wrapping the matching View.

        WHY A SEPARATE FILE: App.xaml holds app-wide resources like value
        converters (BoolToVis, TimeSpanConverter) — a different concern from
        view-resolution mapping. There will be one entry here per section (S1–S9,
        per A-03), so this file's whole purpose is "ViewModel → View," kept
        separate from App.xaml so that file doesn't grow into an unrelated grab-bag
        as sections S2 through S9 are added in later sprints.

        HOW IT'S WIRED: merged into Application.Resources via
        <ResourceDictionary.MergedDictionaries> in App.xaml. Once merged, WPF
        automatically applies the matching DataTemplate any time a ContentControl
        (or similar) is asked to display an object of that DataType — no further
        binding is needed beyond what SectionShellView.xaml already has.
    -->

    <!-- S1 — Report Header (BL-09/BL-10) -->
    <DataTemplate DataType="{x:Type sections:ReportHeaderViewModel}">
        <views:ReportHeaderView/>
    </DataTemplate>

</ResourceDictionary>
